Class XNull

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.xpath.Expression
      • org.apache.xpath.objects.XObject
        • org.apache.xpath.axes.NodeSequence
          • org.apache.xpath.objects.XNodeSet
            • org.apache.xpath.objects.XNull
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, SourceLocator, DTMIterator, PathComponent, ExpressionNode, XPathVisitable

    public class XNull
extends XNodeSet
    This class represents an XPath null object, and is capable of converting the null to other types, such as a string.
    See Also:
